WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:06.490
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I am Ms. Frieren's student.</font>

2
00:00:08.980 --> 00:00:10.410
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You pass.</font>

3
00:00:12.370 --> 00:00:13.340
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Next.</font>

4
00:00:23.080 --> 00:00:27.000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>You're there like the wind</i></font>

5
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.630
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Closing your eyes at sunset</i></font>

6
00:00:31.630 --> 00:00:37.260
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>I wonder what's on your mind</i></font>

7
00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:42.600
<font size="24"><b>{\an8}<font size="35"><font face="Georgia"><font color="#65feff">Beyond Journey's End</font></font></font></b></font>

8
00:00:41.970 --> 00:00:45.980
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>With your eyelids open</i></font>

9
00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:50.570
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Your eyes shone like glass</i></font>

10
00:00:50.570 --> 00:00:57.320
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>It faintly smelled like a sunny day</i></font>

11
00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:08.460
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Clear up the sky. let flowers bloom</i></font>

12
00:01:08.460 --> 00:01:12.670
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky</i></font>

13
00:01:12.670 --> 00:01:17.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Even the rain. when it stops</i></font>

14
00:01:17.050 --> 00:01:22.060
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Will make you shine in the sunlight</i></font>

15
00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:27.440
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Calm the stirring sounds in my heart</i></font>

16
00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:31.480
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>We go like the sunny wind</i></font>

17
00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:35.900
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Go on and fly over that cloud</i></font>

18
00:01:35.900 --> 00:01:40.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Further and further away</i></font>

19
00:01:45.860 --> 00:01:50.870
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Denken the Imperial Mage. 
I know all about you.</font>

20
00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:53.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm honored.</font>

21
00:01:54.670 --> 00:02:02.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">A self-made military mage who rose to be 
the most influential in the northern lands.</font>

22
00:02:02.630 --> 00:02:04.620
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's an oft-heard heroic tale.</font>

23
00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:10.270
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Honestly. I wish I could've met you 
when you were still young.</font>

24
00:02:12.070 --> 00:02:16.850
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">full of drive and ambition.</font>

25
00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:22.700
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I have no interest in burnt-out ashes.</font>

26
00:02:25.340 --> 00:02:27.640
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Or so I believed.</font>

27
00:02:31.080 --> 00:02:33.000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Do you feel differently now?</font>

28
00:02:33.590 --> 00:02:38.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">When you saw me. you thought about 
how you'd fight me. didn't you?</font>

29
00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:45.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Only for a moment. 
I immediately abandoned the idea.</font>

30
00:02:46.490 --> 00:02:49.850
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You pass. There's still a fire in you.</font>

31
00:02:50.770 --> 00:02:53.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Normally it wouldn't even occur 
to someone to fight me.</font>

32
00:02:55.110 --> 00:02:56.100
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Next.</font>

33
00:03:01.590 --> 00:03:02.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You pass.</font>

34
00:03:02.990 --> 00:03:06.590
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What? But we haven't even spoken yet.</font>

35
00:03:07.060 --> 00:03:09.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Do we need to?</font>

36
00:03:10.630 --> 00:03:12.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I guess not.</font>

37
00:03:12.770 --> 00:03:13.690
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Next.</font>

38
00:03:17.740 --> 00:03:20.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Is this some kind of joke?</font>

39
00:03:20.050 --> 00:03:20.970
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What do you mean?</font>

40
00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:23.860
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">This is the first-class mage exam.</font>

41
00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:27.360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What kind of idiot never even sets foot 
into the examination grounds?</font>

42
00:03:28.770 --> 00:03:34.260
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">As you can see. my flesh-and-blood 
body is here. too.</font>

43
00:03:34.260 --> 00:03:35.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I wouldn't want to be disqualified.</font>

44
00:03:35.910 --> 00:03:41.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Throughout the exam period. your actual 
body never left your hometown.</font>

45
00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:44.300
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Are you enjoying some tea right now?</font>

46
00:03:48.410 --> 00:03:49.920
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm surprised.</font>

47
00:03:50.270 --> 00:03:52.250
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Not even Übel noticed.</font>

48
00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:56.220
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You've got guts. You pass.</font>

49
00:03:56.570 --> 00:03:57.720
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Next.</font>

50
00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:03.080
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're Wirbel. captain of 
the Northern Magic Corps.</font>

51
00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:07.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Of the second-class mages I know. 
you're the most combat-oriented.</font>

52
00:04:08.730 --> 00:04:12.780
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">With a single look. you realized 
you couldn't beat me in battle.</font>

53
00:04:13.290 --> 00:04:15.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But that wasn't a judgment made out of fear.</font>

54
00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:21.350
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">An idiot prone to picking fights he can't win
wouldn't even make it to second-class mage.</font>

55
00:04:21.990 --> 00:04:23.450
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's true.</font>

56
00:04:25.190 --> 00:04:26.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Tell me. what's your favorite spell?</font>

57
00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:30.490
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Magic is a tool for killing.</font>

58
00:04:30.490 --> 00:04:32.490
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I neither like nor dislike any spells.</font>

59
00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:35.860
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You pass.</font>

60
00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:36.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Next.</font>

61
00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:44.560
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What did you think when you saw me?</font>

62
00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:50.510
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Um. I thought you were small and cute.</font>

63
00:04:52.840 --> 00:04:56.030
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What's wrong with this year's test-takers?</font>

64
00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:58.110
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You pass.</font>

65
00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:06.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Sense.</font>

66
00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:11.540
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">My apologies. We do have 
a bumper crop this year.</font>

67
00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:16.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I failed.</font>

68
00:05:16.710 --> 00:05:18.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">There's always next time.</font>

69
00:05:18.380 --> 00:05:20.550
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Stop following me.</font>

70
00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:23.130
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Three years. huh?</font>

71
00:05:24.420 --> 00:05:26.810
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Frieren. I passed.</font>

72
00:05:28.810 --> 00:05:30.110
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Well done.</font>

73
00:05:31.630 --> 00:05:32.810
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren.</font>

74
00:05:34.390 --> 00:05:37.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I made it this far because of you two.</font>

75
00:05:38.780 --> 00:05:42.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Finally. I can visit a certain grave 
in my hometown.</font>

76
00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:44.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I see.</font>

77
00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:54.450
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Hey. Fern.</font>

78
00:05:54.450 --> 00:05:56.000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Have you decided yet?</font>

79
00:06:07.130 --> 00:06:08.540
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'd like—</font>

80
00:06:07.370 --> 00:06:08.540
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Old man. I want these.</font>

81
00:06:12.990 --> 00:06:14.130
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Well. well.</font>

82
00:06:18.840 --> 00:06:21.450
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Don't be shy. Eat up.</font>

83
00:06:21.450 --> 00:06:26.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">When I was young. I hardly 
ever got to eat sweet things.</font>

84
00:06:27.060 --> 00:06:28.730
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Thank you.</font>

85
00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:36.080
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>What's going on here?</i></font>

86
00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:41.290
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Have some. young man.</font>

87
00:06:43.400 --> 00:06:45.100
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Thanks. old man.</font>

88
00:06:53.220 --> 00:06:54.230
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Who is he?</font>

89
00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:57.560
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Mr. Denken the Imperial Mage.</font>

90
00:06:58.870 --> 00:07:00.830
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">An imperial mage?</font>

91
00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:07.520
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You mean he's a noble?!</font>

92
00:07:07.520 --> 00:07:11.620
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm sorry for speaking so casually to you.</font>

93
00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:16.370
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's fine. I came to this city 
as a mage like any other.</font>

94
00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:20.950
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But you shouldn't feel obliged 
to treat a stranger like me...</font>

95
00:07:20.950 --> 00:07:23.750
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I have no other use for my money.</font>

96
00:07:23.750 --> 00:07:26.450
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">There must be something.</font>

97
00:07:26.450 --> 00:07:28.500
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">He's right. Don't you have grandchildren?</font>

98
00:07:30.650 --> 00:07:33.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I have no children or grandchildren.</font>

99
00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:37.510
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">My wife passed away when 
I was in my mid-twenties.</font>

100
00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:42.150
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She was always sickly.</font>

101
00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:44.980
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She was the daughter of a frontier noble</font>

102
00:07:44.980 --> 00:07:48.360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">of the Northern Plateau who was 
defeated in a political dispute.</font>

103
00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:54.200
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Back then. I was in need of both 
wealth and influence.</font>

104
00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:57.810
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Those were the only ways I knew to save her.</font>

105
00:07:59.490 --> 00:08:02.000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">When Serie established the 
Continental Magic Association</font>

106
00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:04.550
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">and began offering the privilege.</font>

107
00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:07.830
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">it was just after my wife had already passed.</font>

108
00:08:08.720 --> 00:08:11.670
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'd never felt more powerless.</font>

109
00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:20.940
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's ironic. These days. I could 
order entire nations around.</font>

110
00:08:22.050 --> 00:08:23.150
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Fern.</font>

111
00:08:23.690 --> 00:08:28.570
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">For me. magic was only ever a tool 
to resolve political disputes.</font>

112
00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:37.340
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Tell Frieren she reminded me 
of how fun magic can be.</font>

113
00:08:38.180 --> 00:08:42.000
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The whole reason I became a mage was because</font>

114
00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:44.210
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I admired her deeds in the party of heroes.</font>

115
00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:49.250
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You should tell her that yourself.</font>

116
00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:51.700
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm sure she'd be glad to hear it.</font>

117
00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:56.640
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're right. That's what I'll do.</font>

118
00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:09.600
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The magical city of Äußerst didn't disappoint.</font>

119
00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:11.790
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I bought a bunch of good grimoires.</font>

120
00:09:19.180 --> 00:09:20.530
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Hey. old woman.</font>

121
00:09:21.910 --> 00:09:24.090
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You want those in this basket. right?</font>

122
00:09:27.760 --> 00:09:30.080
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">How could you just ignore her?</font>

123
00:09:30.080 --> 00:09:32.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Honestly. I did think about it a little.</font>

124
00:09:32.760 --> 00:09:34.260
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Just a little?</font>

125
00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:39.420
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm surprised. I thought one of Himmel's 
party members would be...</font>

126
00:09:39.420 --> 00:09:41.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Would be what?</font>

127
00:09:44.200 --> 00:09:46.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">If anything. you surprised me.</font>

128
00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:51.020
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You tried to kill Fern's party 
during the first test. didn't you?</font>

129
00:09:51.020 --> 00:09:53.080
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Fern complained to me about it.</font>

130
00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:55.850
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She said you seemed like someone 
who'd kick a dog out of the way.</font>

131
00:09:56.630 --> 00:09:58.240
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I get that a lot.</font>

132
00:09:59.060 --> 00:10:00.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">All I did was threaten them.</font>

133
00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:06.920
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Though there was one of them whose death 
would probably make the world a better place.</font>

134
00:10:09.110 --> 00:10:12.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'd do anything to protect my hometown.</font>

135
00:10:14.110 --> 00:10:20.050
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I wanted to become a first-class mage for 
the privilege of learning any spell I desired.</font>

136
00:10:20.050 --> 00:10:25.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">With a more powerful spell. 
I can slaughter more demons.</font>

137
00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:33.290
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But even in other parts of the world. 
I do everything I can to help people in need.</font>

138
00:10:33.770 --> 00:10:34.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Why?</font>

139
00:10:37.950 --> 00:10:40.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">My hometown is on the northern frontier.</font>

140
00:10:41.780 --> 00:10:45.270
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">There are countless stories 
about Himmel the Hero there.</font>

141
00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:50.560
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The conquest of the Thousand-Mirror Tower.</font>

142
00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:53.250
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">His battles against Böse the Immortal. 
the Seven Sages of Destruction.</font>

143
00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:55.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">and the Hell Emperor Dragon.</font>

144
00:10:55.750 --> 00:10:59.650
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">When I was a kid. I loved 
those adventure stories.</font>

145
00:11:01.520 --> 00:11:06.130
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But the village elders hardly 
ever talked about them.</font>

146
00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:10.280
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">They'd talk about how he defeated the monsters</font>

147
00:11:10.280 --> 00:11:12.870
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">that attacked the village. 
or how he guarded some merchant.</font>

148
00:11:12.870 --> 00:11:16.330
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">or even how he just helped 
carry stuff like a porter.</font>

149
00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:21.700
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">They were hardly impressive. 
Just a bunch of boring stories.</font>

150
00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:22.940
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's what I thought. anyway.</font>

151
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:29.390
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But you could tell how happy the village 
elders were when they told those stories.</font>

152
00:11:32.680 --> 00:11:35.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">After Himmel the Hero died</font>

153
00:11:35.010 --> 00:11:38.510
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">and the remaining demons started 
acting up. I finally understood.</font>

154
00:11:49.210 --> 00:11:54.720
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The Thousand-Mirror Tower. Böse. 
the Hell Emperor Dragon.</font>

155
00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:58.540
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">even the Demon King—none of that 
had anything to do with my village.</font>

156
00:11:59.630 --> 00:12:03.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Everyone had their hands full 
just maintaining their everyday life.</font>

157
00:12:05.080 --> 00:12:09.420
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">If Himmel the Hero 
hadn't come to my village.</font>

158
00:12:09.420 --> 00:12:14.620
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">then I doubt it'd still be there. 
whether he saved the world or not.</font>

159
00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:17.260
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I see. What are you trying to say?</font>

160
00:12:17.580 --> 00:12:23.550
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Those stories of Himmel's less exciting 
adventures were what guided me here.</font>

161
00:12:26.510 --> 00:12:28.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's all I'm trying to say.</font>

162
00:12:31.310 --> 00:12:33.840
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I've been talking for too long.</font>

163
00:12:34.600 --> 00:12:38.310
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm heading back with those guys.</font>

164
00:12:41.260 --> 00:12:45.030
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren. you should treasure 
the encounters you have.</font>

165
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:49.280
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Death isn't the only goodbye in this life.</font>

166
00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:53.780
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But I guess you already know that.</font>

167
00:13:01.490 --> 00:13:06.610
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren. can't you magic us 
across one by one?</font>

168
00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:10.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Then I'd be left all alone on this side.</font>

169
00:13:10.770 --> 00:13:16.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Himmel. we need to defeat the 
Demon King as soon as possible.</font>

170
00:13:16.010 --> 00:13:19.650
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What point is there in helping people 
in these insignificant ways?</font>

171
00:13:23.140 --> 00:13:25.560
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're right that they're insignificant.</font>

172
00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:30.120
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Such deeds won't change the world.</font>

173
00:13:32.100 --> 00:13:36.840
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But I won't ignore those in need 
right in front of me.</font>

174
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:50.170
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Don't worry. Himmel.</font>

175
00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:53.920
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The world has changed.</font>

176
00:13:57.510 --> 00:14:02.510
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">We'll be granted our privileges tonight. 
and we're each allowed to bring guests.</font>

177
00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:06.130
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Since we have the opportunity. 
let's all go together.</font>

178
00:14:08.620 --> 00:14:11.370
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>She looks really unhappy about the idea.</i></font>

179
00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:16.330
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I was told we're allowed to bring guests.</font>

180
00:14:17.020 --> 00:14:22.830
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm sorry. but Ms. Frieren 
is prohibited per Ms. Serie.</font>

181
00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:24.430
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">For the next thousand years.</font>

182
00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:27.920
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">she is barred from entering any 
Continental Magic Association facility.</font>

183
00:14:28.590 --> 00:14:31.580
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What exactly did she do to deserve this?</font>

184
00:14:32.210 --> 00:14:36.870
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It can't be helped. 
I rubbed Serie the wrong way.</font>

185
00:14:38.390 --> 00:14:41.230
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She's like a child.</font>

186
00:14:41.710 --> 00:14:45.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's not as though 
I wanted to be here anyway.</font>

187
00:14:45.140 --> 00:14:46.890
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'll wait outside.</font>

188
00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:52.370
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'll wait outside. too.</font>

189
00:14:54.350 --> 00:14:55.780
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Hey.</font>

190
00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:07.390
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's the early evening bell.</font>

191
00:15:07.810 --> 00:15:10.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">They should be done receiving 
their privileges soon.</font>

192
00:15:10.710 --> 00:15:11.630
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Yeah.</font>

193
00:15:12.090 --> 00:15:14.360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">A first-class mage.</font>

194
00:15:14.360 --> 00:15:18.250
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The highest level of mage. 
of whom fewer than fifty exist.</font>

195
00:15:18.910 --> 00:15:21.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Fern has grown so much.</font>

196
00:15:25.330 --> 00:15:31.230
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">In this era. Fern will probably 
become a more famous mage than me.</font>

197
00:15:33.550 --> 00:15:34.690
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren.</font>

198
00:15:35.550 --> 00:15:36.810
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm glad.</font>

199
00:15:39.110 --> 00:15:40.250
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Me too.</font>

200
00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:42.430
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Frieren.</font>

201
00:15:45.210 --> 00:15:46.430
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Who is he?</font>

202
00:15:46.430 --> 00:15:48.870
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">A member of the Continental Magic Association.</font>

203
00:15:48.870 --> 00:15:54.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm the first-class mage Lernen. 
one of Ms. Serie's students.</font>

204
00:15:55.510 --> 00:15:58.860
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm sorry for the trouble 
Ms. Serie has caused you.</font>

205
00:15:59.380 --> 00:16:03.150
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's fine. She's always been like that.</font>

206
00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.900
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What is it. Frieren?</font>

207
00:16:10.140 --> 00:16:14.100
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You can see the fluctuations 
in my mana. can't you?</font>

208
00:16:15.970 --> 00:16:20.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're incredibly skilled. 
This peaceful era doesn't suit you.</font>

209
00:16:20.740 --> 00:16:27.120
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're right. I am an old-fashioned mage 
who only knows battle.</font>

210
00:16:27.390 --> 00:16:30.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Serie often says the same thing.</font>

211
00:16:30.010 --> 00:16:33.460
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">If I'd been born during the era in which 
we fought the Demon King's forces.</font>

212
00:16:33.460 --> 00:16:38.670
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I would've gone down in history 
alongside the other famous heroes.</font>

213
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:43.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I see. So what do you want from me?</font>

214
00:16:43.470 --> 00:16:47.890
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The only one of Ms. Serie's students 
whose name is remembered is her first.</font>

215
00:16:47.890 --> 00:16:52.170
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">the Great Mage Flamme 
spoken of in fairy tales.</font>

216
00:16:52.530 --> 00:16:59.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Once I grow old and die. yet another 
proof of her existence will disappear.</font>

217
00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:05.100
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I don't want her to be alone in the future.</font>

218
00:17:05.630 --> 00:17:12.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">even if it means going down in infamy 
as the killer of the legendary mage Frieren.</font>

219
00:17:30.330 --> 00:17:33.430
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I request a duel. Ms. Frieren.</font>

220
00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:37.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I won't fight you. It'd be a waste of time.</font>

221
00:17:38.510 --> 00:17:39.730
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Honestly.</font>

222
00:17:40.410 --> 00:17:45.290
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Mages who only know how to fight 
can be so awkward.</font>

223
00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:49.120
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">There's no need for you to go down in history.</font>

224
00:17:51.460 --> 00:17:53.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Serie will remember you.</font>

225
00:17:57.870 --> 00:17:59.440
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">One last thing.</font>

226
00:18:00.860 --> 00:18:04.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">This field of flowers was conjured by magic.</font>

227
00:18:05.470 --> 00:18:07.130
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">So what?</font>

228
00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:10.190
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It was my master's favorite spell.</font>

229
00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:13.900
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Didn't you call it useless?</font>

230
00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:20.780
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Honestly. Flamme was a failure.</font>

231
00:18:21.900 --> 00:18:26.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Despite all her talent. 
she failed to reach my heights.</font>

232
00:18:28.930 --> 00:18:31.720
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I taught many students after her.</font>

233
00:18:32.550 --> 00:18:36.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Most died without ever reaching my level.</font>

234
00:18:37.720 --> 00:18:39.790
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But it's strange.</font>

235
00:18:40.450 --> 00:18:43.410
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">They were students I chose on a whim.</font>

236
00:18:43.410 --> 00:18:48.290
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">but I can clearly recall each one's 
personality and favorite spell.</font>

237
00:18:50.500 --> 00:18:56.650
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren. for some reason. I've never 
regretted taking on any of my students.</font>

238
00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:00.590
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Even if they never made their mark on history.</font>

239
00:19:02.630 --> 00:19:06.540
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She can't even tell her own students 
how she truly feels.</font>

240
00:19:07.350 --> 00:19:09.650
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">She truly is a child.</font>

241
00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:16.080
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Frieren.</font>

242
00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:19.760
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I received my privilege.</font>

243
00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:21.090
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Shall we go. then?</font>

244
00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:25.090
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Frieren. how did you get 
that injury on your shoulder?</font>

245
00:19:25.470 --> 00:19:28.200
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'd better get it healed at the church.</font>

246
00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:29.600
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Do you think they're still open?</font>

247
00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:33.610
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Truly. we are awkward.</font>

248
00:19:36.470 --> 00:19:39.200
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Both you and I.</font>

249
00:19:42.740 --> 00:19:45.520
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Stark. what are we gonna do today?</font>

250
00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:48.880
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Sorry. but I can't play today.</font>

251
00:19:48.880 --> 00:19:51.620
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Stark. did you have breakfast this morning?</font>

252
00:19:51.620 --> 00:19:53.010
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I already ate.</font>

253
00:19:53.330 --> 00:19:55.800
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Stark. have some of this.</font>

254
00:19:55.800 --> 00:19:57.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Hey. thanks.</font>

255
00:19:58.010 --> 00:20:01.510
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">The path of the warrior 
is long and treacherous.</font>

256
00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:03.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Take care.</font>

257
00:20:03.990 --> 00:20:04.880
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I will.</font>

258
00:20:08.480 --> 00:20:11.390
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's time to say goodbye to Äußerst.</font>

259
00:20:12.100 --> 00:20:15.550
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">People love you 
everywhere you go. Mr. Stark.</font>

260
00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:16.790
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Yeah?</font>

261
00:20:17.420 --> 00:20:21.400
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">By the way. Fern. what spell 
did you end up asking for yesterday?</font>

262
00:20:28.090 --> 00:20:29.390
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Can't you tell?</font>

263
00:20:30.970 --> 00:20:33.320
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Your clothes are clean.</font>

264
00:20:35.180 --> 00:20:38.070
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">And they smell vaguely floral.</font>

265
00:20:38.860 --> 00:20:40.420
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Could it be...</font>

266
00:20:41.070 --> 00:20:44.410
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's a spell to make clothes 
clean and spotless.</font>

267
00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:47.410
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">This will make laundry a breeze.</font>

268
00:20:47.410 --> 00:20:50.430
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Serie the Living Grimoire 
lived up to her name.</font>

269
00:20:50.930 --> 00:20:55.180
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's a legendary-level spell 
from the era of mythology.</font>

270
00:20:56.580 --> 00:20:58.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Well done. Fern.</font>

271
00:20:59.870 --> 00:21:02.070
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That's my student.</font>

272
00:21:05.630 --> 00:21:07.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Of course. Ms. Frieren.</font>

273
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:12.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Ms. Serie didn't seem at all 
happy about it. though.</font>

274
00:21:12.910 --> 00:21:14.830
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Are you insane?</font>

275
00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:17.930
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I'm sure. Serves her right.</font>

276
00:21:21.930 --> 00:21:23.330
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">They're here.</font>

277
00:21:24.390 --> 00:21:27.930
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Frieren. thank you for everything.</font>

278
00:21:28.460 --> 00:21:33.600
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">We didn't pass this time. 
but we'll try again in three years.</font>

279
00:21:33.600 --> 00:21:35.770
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">I see. That's good.</font>

280
00:21:36.270 --> 00:21:37.740
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It's been fun.</font>

281
00:21:37.740 --> 00:21:38.860
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Take care.</font>

282
00:21:39.130 --> 00:21:40.500
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">See you later.</font>

283
00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:42.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Yeah. See you later.</font>

284
00:21:53.950 --> 00:21:58.500
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">That was a rather quick goodbye. 
just like with Sein.</font>

285
00:21:58.500 --> 00:22:00.380
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">And Kraft.</font>

286
00:22:10.670 --> 00:22:15.220
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Himmel. you always say quick goodbyes.</font>

287
00:22:15.700 --> 00:22:16.890
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You think that's strange?</font>

288
00:22:17.250 --> 00:22:20.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It doesn't seem like you.</font>

289
00:22:20.140 --> 00:22:24.140
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It was just a side job. but we still 
spent two weeks traveling together.</font>

290
00:22:24.540 --> 00:22:29.340
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">And we drank with him practically every night.</font>

291
00:22:28.730 --> 00:22:29.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">{\an8}You corrupt priest.</font>

292
00:22:30.800 --> 00:22:31.990
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">You're right.</font>

293
00:22:31.740 --> 00:22:34.290
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}And you alright</i></font>

294
00:22:32.650 --> 00:22:36.850
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">But I'm sure we'll run into each other again 
if we continue traveling.</font>

295
00:22:34.790 --> 00:22:36.790
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}Can you hear me</i></font>

296
00:22:37.580 --> 00:22:43.670
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}Trailing along deserted train tracks</i></font>

297
00:22:38.530 --> 00:22:41.930
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">Tearful goodbyes aren't our style.</font>

298
00:22:43.670 --> 00:22:45.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}Crying excessively</i></font>

299
00:22:46.590 --> 00:22:49.180
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}Wanting you to smile</i></font>

300
00:22:46.900 --> 00:22:50.930
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">After all. it would be embarrassing 
when we met again.</font>

301
00:22:49.180 --> 00:22:55.220
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>{\an8}I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh</i></font>

302
00:22:55.220 --> 00:22:58.940
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>There's something I'd like to tell you</i></font>

303
00:22:58.940 --> 00:23:01.690
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>With words more precious than a goodbye</i></font>

304
00:23:01.690 --> 00:23:07.360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Unremarkable yet special</i></font>

305
00:23:07.360 --> 00:23:10.910
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>See. things that couldn't have been</i></font>

306
00:23:10.910 --> 00:23:13.950
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Seen if it weren't for these eyes</i></font>

307
00:23:13.950 --> 00:23:18.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Why? They begin to overflow</i></font>

308
00:23:18.710 --> 00:23:24.710
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>So. if I were to be born again</i></font>

309
00:23:24.710 --> 00:23:30.630
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>I would surely choose this place once more</i></font>

310
00:23:30.630 --> 00:23:36.640
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>So. if we were to meet again</i></font>

311
00:23:36.640 --> 00:23:42.400
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>I'd never let you go. I'd choose the present</i></font>

312
00:23:42.400 --> 00:23:45.360
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Even if no promises were made</i></font>

313
00:23:45.360 --> 00:23:48.280
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Even if I'm lost in days of loneliness</i></font>

314
00:23:48.280 --> 00:23:54.450
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>Those tears will be alright. 
dawn will surely break</i></font>

315
00:23:54.450 --> 00:23:57.120
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>I'm whispering our lullaby</i></font>

316
00:23:57.120 --> 00:24:01.040
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24"><i>for you to come back home</i></font>

317
00:24:05.850 --> 00:24:08.600
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">It would be embarrassing when we met again.</font>

318
00:24:10.660 --> 00:24:12.950
<font face="Trebuchet MS" size="24">What does that mean?</font>

319
00:24:17.060 --> 00:24:20.060
<font face="Times New Roman">{\an7}<font color="#f7fffa">Episode 28: It Would Be Embarrassing When We Met Again</font></font>
